author: Phoènîx
text:
As close as this description of Rushia's "PA" is to perfection, it still can't describe the sheer cutenes of those words that came out of that mouth. And the impact that those words left on this universe is far too great for mere words to describe.

This is exactly the description that we call "too close but yet toooo far".

author: Zakaker
text:
I was originally planning on studying the origin of the universe through this sound, but the more I listen to it, the more I realize that we were never meant to experience it in the first place. It is a language not conceived for us, hell, most likely not even conceived for this plane of existence. This is the definitive proof that there cannot be something such as a "god", for the very concept of "god" is something we humans can understand and project in our minds, thus elaborating a thought that can then be translated into words; while this discovery demonstrates that "truth" and "origin" both lie beyond the idea of an arkhé and are entirely unfathomable for beings. In fact, at the root of this majestic revelation is absolutely nothing, for whatever is the cause of this result, perceivable to existences as insignificant as us thanks to a mere physical vessel, cannot be considered a "thing", in fact, it cannot be considered at all, and therefore cannot "be."

To this physical vessel, whose purpose lies in a plane different from that of the very concept of "comprehension", I shall pledge my unworthy life, for we don't deserve the ability to choose; instead, we should only act as we are meant to.

Rejoice, my brothers and sisters, for we finally know the purpose of life! Do not be afraid, for the reason why you were born in the first place cannot do harm to its own children! Join, partake in this eternal dance which follows the flow of all that is, and all that is not!
